H0.text: Tissue → organ system → organ → cell is the correct order of relationships in organisms.

H1.text: Organ → cell → organ system → tissue is the correct order of relationships in organisms.

H2.text: Cell → tissue → organ → organ system is the correct order of relationships in organisms.

H3.text: Organ system → organ → cell → tissue is the correct order of relationships in organisms.

A4.text: During cell division, a single cell divides into two daughter cells, leading to the growth of tissue in multicellular organisms.

A5.text: Multicellular behavior is demonstrated by microorganisms that are cloned from a single cell and form visible microbial colonies.
